    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-05-18T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-05-18T11:00:00-05:00" n="334"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d334">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00 R 29/216: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wallace</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-05-18T17:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 18, 1920—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 18—1:24 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1169. B–91. For Davis. Supplementing my B–82.</p>
                <p>Commission decided yesterday ask all government[s] signing treaty, whether
                    ratified or not, to report to Commission what progress made in making up claims,
                    what doubtful questions upon which they desired rulings, nature of proof they
                    proposed to such [<hi rend="italic">sic</hi>]; also to submit complete files of
                    evidence in specific cases of various kinds for consideration as test cases, all
                    for the purpose of enabling Commission to formulate regulations for presentation
                    of claims; also [to] request suggestion as to fixing definite time limit for
                    filing claims with Commission. Foregoing request not formal, but merely
                    practical useful preliminary for assistance work of Commission. Foregoing for
                    your information. Commission request when drafted will probably be sent to
                    Embassy. Boyden.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wallace</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
